<br>
For both of those weapon types, it seems idiotic to take your spec past 34(sword) or 29(hammer)  <br>
<br>
In the hammer spec:<br>
<br>
The 34 style(Thor's Answer) requires you to perform Revenge, which requires you to block.  It seems that most Skalds use 2h weapons because of the increased damage available with those weapons, and our inability to train a shield or use a medium or large shield.<br>
<br>
The 39 style(Lambast) requires you to parry, which is broken in RvR and is hardly ever trained to a high lvl because it is broken.  Also, after performing it, you have a defensive penalty, which doesn't make ANY sense if you konw anything about melee combat.  After you have parried an opponents attack, they are in a horrid position to strike you.<br>
<br>
The 44 style(Conquer) is great.  Lovely damage bonus and end cost, nothing to complain about, but you pick up two pretty much worthless styles to get to it.<br>
<br>
The 50 style(Mjolnir's Fury) requires Thor's Answer, which we have allready shown isn't going to happen.<br>
<br>
Now onto Swords:<br>
<br>
The 34 style(Polar Rift) is great.  Would be nice to see only a medium cost on end, but otherwise is fine for a 34 style.<br>
<br>
The 39 style(Niord's Fury) requires Frost Cut.  I have never used Frost Cut, ever.  I don't use a shield, so I CAN'T block.  I don't use a shield because I can only use a small shield.  Even if I used a shield, I only have a 5% chance to block.  Everything else about this style is great, the end cost and the damage bonus, and the attack bonus.<br>
<br>
The 44 style(Sif's Revenge) requires Rush, which requires Reinforcement.  I would love to be able to use this style, but sadly I won't be able to because Parry is broken, which is required to get off Reinforcement.<br>
<br>
The 50 style(Ragnarok) seems great until you think about the logic of it.  I'm going to be performing a positional style, that requires me to be behind someone.  I only get a medium attack bonus to it.  Why?  The person I'm attacking CAN'T see me.  He/She has NO defense.  I also recieve a defense penalty.  I just hit this person in the BACK with my best style and I receive a penalty?  That and my damage bonus is only medium?  On the top style that I can ever hope to do with a sword?  Why exactly would I ever want to go to 50 for this?<br>
<br>
Now on to Axe:<br>
<br>
The 34 Style(Midnight Sun) isn't going to happen.  You have to do Valkyrie's Shield, which requires you to block. <br>
<br>
The 39 Style(Glacial Movement) is a pretty good positional style.  Nothing really wrong with it.<br>
<br>
The 44 Style(Arctic Rift) requires Evernight.  So you have to get behind your target.  Other than that, this thing rocks!  If I'm an Axe Skald, I'm going to spam this all over RvR.  Low fatigue costs on both, and a high damage on Arctic Rift.  Great frickin style.<br>
<br>
The 50 Style(Tyr's Fury) requires Havoc.  So you have to be in front of your target.  That has to be the funniest thing ever.  I would spam this on a tank while assisting someone with real HPs.  Both of the styles have high damage bonuses, only medium end costs, and Tyr's Fury has a high attack bonus.<br>
<br>
So it seems that you guys have basically made it STUPID for Skalds to use anything other than an Axe.  Why even offer us the other two weapons when you can't use all of your top three styles?<br>
<br>
THIS IS NOT A CALL FOR A NERF ON AXES!  Please do not think that.  This is just a request to bring the Sword and Hammer styles to a comparable lvl with the Axe.  I like using my 2h sword, and would prefer not to have to respec it at 40.<br>
<br>
Fixing Parry in RvR would go a long way to making some of these styles usable.  Maybe even giving us Medium shields, so we have a better chance of blocking, although I think we would probably prefer to have the styles requiring Block moved to a positional or Parry based if Parry were fixed.<br>
<br>
I'm not even going to go into the Battle Song line, with a much resisted 34 lvl Shout, and no reason to spec to 50 unless you want to solo for some reason and need that Heavenly Song of Rest.  I think it would make sense for an offensive character to have a 45+ lvl offensive spell, but hey, I guess our 700rng Damage Add must make up for it since it is at 46.<br>
<br>
I do appreciate you fixing the Damage Add stacking problems, that was way cool of you.  Does that affect the R.A. also?<br>
<br>
Matt Jones<br>
