No &quot;to hit&quot; bonus on the second part of a style chain is horrendous. Even in PvE where parry is not broken, I found better to only use reinforcment, then do polar rift or, even better the assault chain (+med to hit bonus) instead of whiffing on Rush. <br>
The parry requirement + the no &quot;to hit&quot; bonus make the parry chain completely unreliable. I could MAYBE take the risk to Rush if the effect on Sif's was more valuable  than a bleed that overwrites the effect of the first style in the line (!!!!).<br>
No bonus to hit and a medium penalty to defense on the second style of a reactionary chain ? Please ...<br>
<br>
Sword's redeeming grace is the good PvE anytime combo (assault+ice storm, while lowish on the damage side, is good for efficient hunting with the low endurance cost), and the spammable Polar Rift in zerg situations where tactical/positional issues are secondary and endurance regen is available.<br>
Reactives ? No evade chain, the block chain is irrelevant for skalds, the parry chain is flawed (poor design with 2 bleed effects and rush is way too unreliable).<br>
Positionals ? The side chain is OK, but you get nastier side or back chains with many other styles (stuns ...)<br>
